--- body ---
## Context
Ticket 0182 asked whether the manuscript claim — that the three pre-2007
intellectual traditions (environmental economics, development economics,
burden-sharing) were structurally separate — survives a density-conditioned
null once the labelling is kept clean of community detection. Two rounds of
testing killed it as a *corpus* finding: the strong separation of the
Louvain-anchored partition is circular (the partition is optimised on the
very graph the null tests); fixing tradition membership a priori from the
founding works is degenerate, because outside environmental economics those
works barely appear as citation nodes in the thin pre-2007 slice; and a
temporal cross-tradition citation-coupling test found no integration break
at crystallization surviving a density control. The early corpus is too
sparse to bear a quantitative test of the separation. The separation rests
on the intellectual-historical record. This is reported as an honest
NEGATIVE RESULT, not hidden.

## Decision (author-validated 2026-07-08)
Frank retreat, not a numbers-hedged descriptive-consistency claim.

## Actions (done)
1. Retreated the three strong loci in `content/manuscript.qmd` to the honest
   position — A.1 (the confirmatory tripod), section 1.5 ("occupy separate
   lineages sharing almost no co-citation edges"), and A.5 ("the three
   traditions hardly read one another"). No null-model / z-score /
   degree-preserving / community-detection jargon in the confessing
   sentences; the separation now rests on the intellectual history, with a
   note that a fuller early record may make the test possible later.
2. Added one qualitative negative-result paragraph near A.5: we tried a
   co-citation division, a sparsity-conditioned control and a
   cross-tradition citation-over-time check; none is conclusive before 2007
   because coverage is sparse and the founding works barely enter the corpus.
   Framed as a virtue, pointing to the reproducibility materials generically.
3. Preserved the annexe's co-citation evidence for the other periods (the
   full-span community persistence, the method description): the retreat is
   only about the pre-2007 separation claim.

## Relevant files
- `content/manuscript.qmd` — A.1, section 1.5, A.5 (the three reworded loci + the new paragraph)

